history.content: Hi Folks, I realized what had happened with EECS C106A (corsslisting issues I won't burden you with) and EECS 126. I've fixed some of those, but the main reason I'm finding folks are unable to enroll is the subsections they are selecting have full waitlsits. Lecture, lab and discussions have to be open or have waitlist room to be able to waitlist for the course. Hope this helps! If you're still having issues email ee-scheudling@berkeley.edu and I'll look into it further for you.

Hi,
I am a current freshman, intending to major in cs. My enrollment time for class sign up was 1:00 pm today (April 28). I was trying to enroll into EECS 106A, and as a back up EECS 126, but I was unable to waitlist into either class. On my enrollment center and classes.berkeley.edu it says that there are waitlist spots available and discussion/ lab spots open. Whenever I click enroll, it says that I can't add the class because there are no waitlist spots open, when on the website it says there are. I wanted to take cs 61c, but since the rule changed recently that only declared cs majors can take 61c/ cs upper divs, I can't take any cs classes. I was hoping I would at least get eecs 106a or eecs 126. I was wondering if there is any way for me to add these classes to my course schedule?
